         <abstract>
            <p>The traditional economic order quantity (EOQ) formulation of the bond issue size problem assumes constant debt needs per period. This paper presents an alternative decision procedure that provides more efficient decisions than the EOQ formulation when debt needs are growing or are otherwise irregular.</p>
         </abstract>
